  {
    "id": "koc2012-q008",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "number-systems",
    "subtopic": "decimal-to-binary",
    "stem": "The binary conversion of decimal 30 is:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "11110",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "10110",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "10001",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "00111",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "30 = 16 + 8 + 4 + 2, so bits 4,3,2,1 are set and bit 0 is clear, giving 11110. Check the distractor: 10110 = 16 + 4 + 2 = 22, not 30.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
